The paper deals with feedback coding and hybrid ARQ systems, which are primarily studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses rate-compatible sphere-packing (RCSP) analysis, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses error correction codes and decoding error rates, which are studied in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of RCSP analysis in cases where packets have deadlines, which falls under the computer communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
